topIssues.title: pino-pretty errors in export builds from bun - replace pino with adze
topIssues.author: lalalune
topIssues.body:
Our logger is not compatible with the bun binary compilation and build process. Since its built into the core, its very hard to get into and override, so we should rip it out and use a bun compatible logger instead. After some research, I think this is a good option: https://adzejs.com/

We could also just roll our own logging, but then we need color formatting and all that and I'd rather just have something that already works and is easy to drop in.

Please replace pino and all pino-related dependencies with adze and make sure everything works and all tests still pass @claude

topIssues.author: fuhaooo
topIssues.body: **Describe the bug** The agent created using `elizaos create ` on Windows WSL does not respond to messages in the front-end GUI. When I send the message "hello, what's your name?" to the default agent, there is no response from the agent. **To Reproduce** 1. Set up ElizaOS in a Windows WSL environment. 2. Create an agent using the command: `elizaos create `. 3. Set up the Google Generative AI API key in the environment. 4. Run `elizaos start` to start the project. 5. topIssues.title: `elizaos publish` fails with zod module error in newly created plugins
topIssues.author: linear
topIssues.body:
\## Summary

The \`elizaos publish\` command fails immediately after creating a new plugin with \`elizaos create --type plugin\`, throwing a "Cannot find module 'zod/v3'" error from @langchain/core.

\## Environment

\- \*\*elizaOS CLI version\*\*: 1.3.0

\- \*\*Bun version\*\*: 1.2.15

\- \*\*OS\*\*: macOS arm64

\- \*\*Location\*\*: Fresh plugin created via CLI

\## Steps to Reproduce

1\. Run \`elizaos create --type plugin testing -y\`

2\. Navigate to the created plugin directory: \`cd plugin-testing\`

3\. Run \`elizaos publish -h\` (or any publish command)

\## Expected Behavior

The publish command should display help information or execute without module errors.

\## Actual Behavior

Command fails with error:

\`\`\`

error: Cannot find module 'zod/v3' from '/Users/yungalgo/Desktop/plugin-testing/node_modules/@langchain/core/dist/runnables/base.js'

\`\`\`

\## Full Terminal Output

\`\`\`bash

yungalgo@machine \~/desktop $ elizaos -v

1.3.0

yungalgo@machine \~/desktop $ elizaos create --type plugin testing -y

Warning: changing "testing" to "plugin-testing" to conform to plugin naming conventions

│

◇ Copying plugin template completed

│

│

◇ ✓ Dependencies installed successfully

◇ Installing dependencies completed

✓ Plugin "plugin-testing" created successfully!

Next steps:

cd plugin-testing

bun run build *# Build the plugin*

Common commands:

elizaos dev *# Start development mode with hot reloading*

elizaos start *# Start in production mode*

yungalgo@machine \~/desktop $ cd plugin-testing

yungalgo@machine \~/desktop/plugin-testing $ elizaos publish -h

\[2025-07-21 20:29:34\] INFO: Using local @elizaos/cli installation

error: Cannot find module 'zod/v3' from '/Users/yungalgo/Desktop/plugin-testing/node_modules/@langchain/core/dist/runnables/base.js'

Bun v1.2.15 (macOS arm64)

\`\`\`

\## Analysis

The issue appears to be a missing or incorrect dependency resolution where:

1\. The plugin template includes @langchain/core as a dependency

2\. @langchain/core expects 'zod/v3' to be available

3\. The zod package is either not installed or not at the correct version that exports a 'v3' subpath

\## Potential Solutions

1\. Add explicit zod dependency to the plugin template's package.json

2\. Update @langchain/core to a version that doesn't require 'zod/v3'

3\. Ensure proper peer dependency resolution during plugin creation

4\. Check if this is a Bun-specific module resolution issue

\## Priority

High - This blocks plugin publishing workflow immediately after creation

\## Additional Notes

\- The plugin creation itself completes successfully

\- Dependencies install without errors during creation

\- The error only appears when trying to use the publish command

\- This affects the out-of-the-box experience for new plugin developers

topIssues.title: Eddy - Devrel Agent Notes
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body: The DevRel Agent should always provide the most up-to-date content from the documentation, even if updates were made as recently as yesterday.” The goal is to ensure that when I ask questions, the agent reflects the latest changes and doesn’t rely on outdated versions of the docs. My understanding is thats not possible just yet. If we add a new doc, it will be taken into consideration but not if an existing file/doc is changed.

topPRs.title: fix: gitignores missing in plugin starter
topPRs.author: ChristopherTrimboli
topPRs.body:
## Problem
   When creating plugins with `elizaos create`, the .gitignore file was not included in the published npm package. This could lead to accidentally committing and pushing sensitive files like .env to GitHub.

   ## Solution
   - Added .gitignore to the files array in plugin template package.json files
   - Created .npmignore for CLI to explicitly include template dot files
   - Added security warning after plugin creation
   
   ## Testing
   - Created new plugin with updated CLI
   - Verified .gitignore is included in npm package using `npm pack --dry-run`
   - Confirmed sensitive files are properly excluded from version control
